PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a 15x10-inch jelly-roll pan. COMBINE flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl. Beat sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in eggs and vanilla extract; gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels. Spread into prepared pan. BAKE for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack.